{"questionId":"3857811","questionHtml":"<p>A negatively charged particle is stationary halfway between two horizontal charged plates. The plates are separated by a distance <em>d</em> with potential difference <em>V</em> between them.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/200a86799788d5c3679d2bdeb014eda32bf3227b.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the magnitude of the electric field and direction of the electric field at the position of the particle?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"width:346px;height:179px;border-color:#000000;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:132.05px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Magnitude of</strong><br><strong>electric field</strong>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:137.95px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Direction of</strong><br><strong>electric field</strong>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">A.</td>\n<td style=\"width:132.05px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:137.95px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">up</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:45px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"width:132.05px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:137.95px;text-align:center;\">up</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"width:132.05px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:137.95px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">down</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:29px;\">\n<td style=\"width:45px;height:29px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"width:132.05px;height:29px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:137.95px;height:29px;text-align:center;\">down</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3857811","referenceCode":"23M.1A.HL.TZ1.31","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A negatively charged particle is stationary halfway between two horizontal charged plates. The plates are separated by a distance d with potential difference V between them. What i","paper":"1A","level":"HL","questionNumber":"31","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D.2 Electric and magnetic fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}